msgid "maxframe.learn.preprocessing.minmax\\_scale"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:1 of
msgid "Transform features by scaling each feature to a given range."
msgstr "通过将每个特征缩放到给定范围来变换特征。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:3 of
msgid ""
"This estimator scales and translates each feature individually such that "
"it is in the given range on the training set, i.e. between zero and one."
msgstr ""
"此估计器独立地缩放和平移每个特征，使其在训练集上的取值范围为给定区间，即"
"在零和一之间。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:7 of
msgid "The transformation is given by (when ``axis=0``)::"
msgstr "变换公式如下（当 ``axis=0`` 时）："

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:12 of
msgid "where min, max = feature_range."
msgstr "其中 min, max = feature_range。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:14 of
msgid "The transformation is calculated as (when ``axis=0``)::"
msgstr "变换计算方式如下（当 ``axis=0`` 时）："

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:19 of
msgid ""
"This transformation is often used as an alternative to zero mean, unit "
"variance scaling."
msgstr "这种变换通常用作零均值、单位方差缩放的替代方法。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:22 of
msgid "Read more in the :ref:`User Guide <preprocessing_scaler>`."
msgstr "更多内容请参见 :ref:`用户指南 <preprocessing_scaler>`。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:24 of
msgid ""
"*minmax_scale* function interface to "
":class:`~sklearn.preprocessing.MinMaxScaler`."
msgstr ""
"*minmax_scale* 函数接口对应于 :class:`~sklearn.preprocessing.MinMaxScaler"
"`。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale of
msgid "参数"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:28 of
msgid "The data."
msgstr "数据。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:30 of
msgid "Desired range of transformed data."
msgstr "变换后数据的期望范围。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:32 of
msgid ""
"Axis used to scale along. If 0, independently scale each feature, "
"otherwise (if 1) scale each sample."
msgstr ""
"用于缩放的轴。如果为 0，则独立缩放每个特征；否则（如果为 1）则缩放每个"
"样本。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:35 of
msgid ""
"Set to False to perform inplace scaling and avoid a copy (if the input is"
" already a numpy array)."
msgstr "设置为 False 可执行就地缩放并避免复制（如果输入已经是 numpy 数组）。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale of
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:39 of
msgid ""
"* **X_tr** (*ndarray of shape (n_samples, n_features)*) -- The "
"transformed data. * *.. warning:: Risk of data leak* -- Do not use "
":func:`~sklearn.preprocessing.minmax_scale` unless you know   what you "
"are doing. A common mistake is to apply it to the entire data   *before* "
"splitting into training and test sets. This will bias the   model "
"evaluation because information would have leaked from the test   set to "
"the training set.   In general, we recommend using   "
":class:`~sklearn.preprocessing.MinMaxScaler` within a   :ref:`Pipeline "
"<pipeline>` in order to prevent most risks of data   leaking: `pipe = "
"make_pipeline(MinMaxScaler(), LogisticRegression())`."
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:39 of
msgid ""
"**X_tr** (*ndarray of shape (n_samples, n_features)*) -- The transformed "
"data."
msgstr "**X_tr** (*ndarray of shape (n_samples, n_features)*) -- 变换后的数据。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:40 of
msgid ""
"*.. warning:: Risk of data leak* -- Do not use "
":func:`~sklearn.preprocessing.minmax_scale` unless you know what you are "
"doing. A common mistake is to apply it to the entire data *before* "
"splitting into training and test sets. This will bias the model "
"evaluation because information would have leaked from the test set to the"
" training set. In general, we recommend using "
":class:`~sklearn.preprocessing.MinMaxScaler` within a :ref:`Pipeline "
"<pipeline>` in order to prevent most risks of data leaking: `pipe = "
"make_pipeline(MinMaxScaler(), LogisticRegression())`."
msgstr ""
"*.. 警告:: 数据泄露风险* -- 除非你知道自己在做什么，否则不要使用 :func:`~"
"sklearn.preprocessing.minmax_scale`。一个常见的错误是在将数据拆分为训练集"
"和测试集 *之前* 应用它。这会导致模型评估产生偏差，因为信息会从测试集泄露"
"到训练集中。通常，我们建议在 :ref:`Pipeline <pipeline>` 中使用 :class:`~"
"sklearn.preprocessing.MinMaxScaler` 来防止大多数数据泄露风险：`pipe = "
"make_pipeline(MinMaxScaler(), LogisticRegression())`。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:52 of
msgid ":py:obj:`MinMaxScaler`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:53 of
msgid ""
"Performs scaling to a given range using the Transformer API (e.g. as part"
" of a preprocessing :class:`~sklearn.pipeline.Pipeline`)."
msgstr ""
"使用 Transformer API 执行给定范围的缩放（例如作为预处理 :class:`~sklearn."
"pipeline.Pipeline` 的一部分）。"

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:56 of
msgid "备注"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.learn.preprocessing._data.min_max_scaler.minmax_scale:57 of
msgid ""
"For a comparison of the different scalers, transformers, and normalizers,"
" see :ref:`examples/preprocessing/plot_all_scaling.py "
"<sphx_glr_auto_examples_preprocessing_plot_all_scaling.py>`."
msgstr ""
"有关不同缩放器、变换器和归一化器的比较，请参见 :ref:`examples/"
"preprocessing/plot_all_scaling.py <sphx_glr_auto_examples_preprocessing_"
"plot_all_scaling.py>`。"

